JFIF file seems to have unsupported meta data that is disliked by ImageIO.

This causes it to generate funny Mime Type.

You can test [this image|^genuine-engraved logo on side cover.jpg] using this wiki markup:
{code}
!genuine-engraved logo on side cover.jpg|thumbnail!
{code}

Need to have a better error message that informs users about this, current error message only says:
{noformat}
Could not generate thumbnail: Image file format not supported
{noformat}

Perhaps we should say Confluence was unable to retrieve meta data from the JPEG file. Either this or we update [the documentation|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Image+File+Formats] saying that we only support EXIF standard.

